  "texts": [
    "Their methodology synergizes two DL models: Mask R-CNN for precise object detection of ichthyolith regions and EfficientNet-V2 for subsequent, more accurate classification of these detected regions into distinct classes.",
    "This dual-model system demonstrates a high degree of accuracy and shows potential for practical applications in determining depositional ages and environments of deep-sea sediments.",
    "Furthermore, the system accurately estimates detected ichthyolith lengths, highlighting its utility in marine ecosystem evolution research.",
    "The limitation of the approach lies in its reliance on a relatively small dataset for training the Mask R-CNN model, which, while sufficient for detecting contours of potential teeth, falls short in accurately distinguishing the 2009) 1000-class output and introducing layers specific to the radiolarian dataset, which allowed the model to better capture the morphological features unique to radiolarian species.",
    "The fine-tuning of the weight-learn and bias-learn rate factors helped emphasize new data relevance over pre-existing weights, optimizing the model's adaptability to this specialized dataset."
  ]
}